        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>remaining soy sauce</strong>, <strong>rice vinegar </strong>and <strong>peanut butter </strong>to the <strong>chilli oil </strong>with a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong> and a good grind of <strong>black pepper</strong> and give everything a good mix up – this is your<strong> sauce</strong></p><p>Once the noodles are done, add a splash of the<strong> starchy noodle water</strong> to the <strong>sauce</strong> – this is your <strong>Sichuan-style chilli sauce</strong></p><p>Tip: You want the sauce to be a single cream consistency so it can coat all of the noodles!</p>",
